Enum
--------
(Enumeration)


It is a new data type which is supported in Typescript.
It is used to define a set of named constants.
Typescript supports both numeric and string values.
use enum keyword.

enums makes easy to change value in future.
It reduces errors which are caused by mistyping.
It exists during compilation time only, so no memory is allocated.

Typescript Enums
----------------------------
Numeric Enums
String Enums
Heterogenous Enums


Numeric Enums
---------------------------
These are number based enums which stores values as numbers.

enum Flowers
{
Rose,
Lilly,
Sunflower,
Marie Gold
}
-----
enum Flowers
{
Rose,
Lilly,
Sunflower,
MarieGold
}
console.log(Flowers);

enum Flowers1
{
Rose,
Lilly=11,
Sunflower,
MarieGold
}
console.log(Flowers1);


String enums
----------------------
enum Cities
{
Bombay="MUM",
Delhi="DEL",
Chennai="CHN",
Hyderabad="HYD"
}
console.log(Cities.Delhi);
console.log(Cities);


Heterogenous enums
-------------------------------

enum Cities1
{
Bombay=2,
Delhi=1,
Chennai="CHN",
Hyderabad="HYD"
}
console.log(Cities1);

-------------